'''''Star Wars'' 25''' is the twenty-fifth issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Archie Goodwin]], illustrated by [[Carmine Infantino]], and first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[April 24]], [[1979]]. It features the story "'''Siege at Yavin!'''," in which the [[Great Temple/Legends|Rebel base]] comes under [[Yavin blockade|attack]] by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]].

==Publisher's summary==
''An Imperial blockade may spell doom for the Rebel base.''

==Plot summary==
{{Quote|Let the ''Sith Lord'' follow his 'Force,' scrambling about the galaxy, seeking those who ''shamed'' him in the Death Star battle&mdash;we're beating the Alliance ''here''!|[[Orman Tagge/Legends|Orman Tagge]]|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 25">[[Star Wars (1977) 25|''Star Wars'' (1977) 25]]</ref>}}
After their escape from [[The Wheel/Legends|the Wheel]], [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] arrive at [[Centares/Legends|Centares]] to trade in the ''[[Spoilt Sport]]'' for a more practical and less traceable [[Luke Skywalker's scout craft|ship]]. As they leave the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], they discover that a [[House of Tagge/Legends|House of Tagge]] [[Mining Explorer]] is on its way to [[Yavin Prime/Legends|Yavin]]. Knowing the Tagges' ties with the Empire and fearing for the security of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] base on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], they follow them and investigate further.

They discover that the Mining Explorer is transporting Imperial [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighters]] to the planet Yavin and hiding the fighters in the thick [[Gas giant/Legends|gas giant]]. Luke and Leia realize that this can only mean danger for the Rebel base nearby and rush to alert them, but they are intercepted by an Imperial patrol.

